product_name: NYX Professional MakeupButtermelt Glaze Skin Tint SPF 30
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackDull skin? Get GLAZED! NYX Professional Makeup Buttermelt Glaze Skin Tint, with Shea & Mango Butter plus Niacinamide, gives you glazed donut skin & SPF 30 in dewy sheer shades!
details: DetailsBenefitsGo from skin that's lookin dull to skin that's givin' GLAZE!You’ll be lookin’ butta than ever with this 93% skincare tint infused with Shea Butter, Mango Butter, & NiacinamideThis non greasy glaze leaves skin smooth and protected! You butta believe this formula has no white cast and even resists fading for a soft glow glazed lookGet glowing glazed donut skin & SPF 30 protection in a skincare-based formula that wears for up to 12H!Now in ten sheer buttalicious shades, this glaze has got you butta’d down in benefitsKey IngredientsShea, Mango Butter and NiacinamideItem 2634233How To UseGet ready to glaze it up! Shake well and dispense a generous amount of product onto skin. Blend that butta into your skin with fingers, a makeup sponge or brush. Watch as the formula melts right in for healthy even skin tone and texture. Customize your coverage by applying a thin layer to skin to build up that buttery glaze! Glue it all down with The Face Glue Setting Spray!IngredientsWater, Glycerin, Caprylyl Methicone, Dimethicone, Silica, Butyloctyl Salicylate, Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone, Niacinamide, Propanediol, Dimethicone/PEG-10/15 Crosspolymer, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Mangifera Indica (Mango) Seed Butter, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter, Simethicone, Sodium Chloride, Sodium Citrate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Silica Silylate, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Aluminum Hydroxide, Adenosine, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Dipropylene Glycol, Caprylyl Glycol, Citric Acid, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Maltodextrin, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Tocopherol, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Phenoxyethanol, Chlorphenesin, Fragrance, Limonene. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide, Iron Oxides. (F.I.L. V70049616/21).
how_to_use: Get ready to glaze it up! Shake well and dispense a generous amount of product onto skin. Blend that butta into your skin with fingers, a makeup sponge or brush. Watch as the formula melts right in for healthy even skin tone and texture. Customize your coverage by applying a thin layer to skin to build up that buttery glaze! Glue it all down with The Face Glue Setting Spray!

reviews.headline: Returned after one use
reviews.comments:
I went into the store hoping they had Morphe Tinted moisturizer, which they stopped carrying in store. Had an employee suggest this instead.
Absolutely did not like it at all! It's really heavy and cakey, doesn't dry down so you sweat underneath it. Its also very matte which i dont care for. That being said it didn't have great coverage and it also didnt mix well with concealer or powder. Patchy and horrible! Final straw is i got the light medium shade that said cool, but it oxidized orange like a an ugly fake tanner on me.
Had to return it the next day.

Decent product overall. The one drawback is it leaves my skin a little tacky. The coverage is super light so it would be great for the pool. Overall, if you're looking for just light coverage for a day at the pool or beach, it would be work great.

reviews.comments: Gave me a bad chemical burn.. I don't ever really try new products on my face, and this made me remember why! I was able to restore my skin barrier. Just use with caution please!

reviews.headline: Great!
reviews.comments: This has just the right amount of coverage. Not greasy and the sunscreen is a plus. The price is amazing and I don't leave the house without it.

reviews.headline: Absolutely love this product!!!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This Buttermelt Glaze Soft Glow Skin Tint is my new favorite product! I love that it melts seamlessly into my skin, instantly leaving it feeling refreshed and rehydrated. It gives me just the alright amount of coverage for a natural, subtle glowing complexion! I love the easy-squeeze convenient tube. And of course, the fact that it is SPF 30, so I know my skin is being protected! Definitely recommend, I will be purchasing this and will add it to my routine!!!

faceoff_positive.comments:
As a consumer reviewing the NYX Buttermelt Glaze Soft Glow Skin Tint, I would highlight several key aspects:

Packaging
The product comes in a sleek, lightweight tube that makes it easy to dispense the right amount of product. The design is appealing and fits well in any makeup bag, making it great for travel.

Texture and Application
The texture of the skin tint is creamy and smooth, blending effortlessly into the skin. It feels lightweight and comfortable, providing a second-skin effect. I found that it applies well with both fingers and a brush, allowing for versatile application techniques. 
Coverage
The coverage is sheer to medium, which is perfect for those who prefer a natural look. It evens out the skin tone without feeling heavy or cakey. If you're looking for something that allows your skin to shine through while still providing a bit of coverage, this product is a great choice.

 Finish
The soft glow finish is a standout feature. It gives the skin a radiant, dewy look without being overly shiny. This makes it ideal for daily wear, as it enhances the skin's natural glow rather than masking it.

Longevity
In terms of wear time, I found that it held up reasonably well throughout the day. Depending on your skin type, you may want to set it with a powder for added longevity, especially in warmer weather.

Shade Range
NYX typically offers a decent range of shades, and the Buttermelt Glaze Skin Tint is no exception. It's important to swatch and find the right match for your skin tone, as the sheer coverage can affect how the tint appears on different skin types.

Overall Impression
Overall, I would recommend the NYX Buttermelt Glaze Soft Glow Skin Tint for anyone looking for a lightweight, natural finish product. It's perfect for everyday wear and can easily be built up for more coverage if needed. The affordable price point makes it accessible, and it's a great option for those who want a quick and easy solution for achieving a fresh, glowing complexion.
faceoff_positive.headline: I love this product!

faceoff_negative.comments:
Let me start this by saying that i have combo / normal skin with my skin leaning slightly more oily in the summer, please take note that I DO NOT HAVE SENSITIVE SKIN. I can usually wear any skincare or makeup products without issues, and have never had any type of allergic reaction to a skincare or makeup product. 

I had swatched this on my wrist in store right after it released, and it really did glide on like butter and blend out to the most beautiful, smooth canvas. 
My shade was out of stock, so I went home excitedly purchased this. 
The day after it arrived I had serval appointments and was in a time chunch trying to get out of the door in time so I had to do my makeup in the car. Within seconds of applying this product to my face it immediately started burning. 
Since I was in the car & had no way to remove it i was unable to remove the product, by the time i arrived at my appointment 1.5 hrs later my entire face was red as a beet & burning, my right eye was bloodshot & burning so bad i couldnt see out of it for the next 24 hrs. 
I removed this product as soon as i was able to get to a bathroom, maybe 2-3 hours after applying it and for the next 3 days my skin and right eye would burn. 
I dont know what is in this product but it gave me a chemical burn on my face. Its been over a week since the incident and i still cannot wear makeup on my face. 
The skin on my face is peeling like it would if I had a serious sunburn and is so sensitive. All ive been able to do is slather it in my face creams, I cannot even use my normal serums or toners due to the burn. 
This has been some of the worst skin related pain I've ever had, the onky thing I have ever experienced that even comes close to this is years ago when I got so sunburned that i had second degree burns all over my body & i had Sun poisoning. 
I immediately returned this product and am now nursing my skin back to health. 

Products I used under my makeup that day where the same ones ive used for nearly 2 years & have used under at least 10 different foundations, concealers and skin tints. 
And my skincare routine is extremely basic, I use the Cosrx Snail serum and for moisturizer I use either Coxrx gel snail cream and the Khiels ultra face cream depending on how much hydration I need, sometimes during the summer I also use the glow recipe watermelon toner (i did NOT use it the day of this incident, only the snail serum & gel cream). 
I have never ever had any issues with this skincare combo affecting my makeup or cuasing a reaction. 
I also did not use a primer on one half of my face (both halves burned equally) bc i wanted to see how well it wore with & without my normal primer, the primer I used on one side was the elf og gripping priner, I have used this primer since it released & with at least 10 different base makeup products without any kind of issue & again, both sides of my face burnt equally, however the side WITHOUT the primer was the side that had eye burning. 

This product has cuased me so much pain and damaged my skin, my fact looks redder than a lobster and hurts more than sun poisoning. 

Did it wear beautifully for the 2-3 hours i had it on? Yes, it was gorgeous. My skin was so smooth & looked absolutely flawless (for about 2 hours until i removed it & revealed the burnt, damaged, lobster colored skin under it). 
Would I recommend or try this product again? ABSOLUTELY NOT!!!

TRY AT YOUR OWN RISK!!!!
faceoff_negative.headline: ABSOLUTELY NOT!!
